      "rooted and built up in Him and established in the faith, as you have been taught, abounding in it with thanksgiving.",
    scriptureReference: "Colossians 2:7 (NKJV)",
    body: "It did not end the previous day. Dr. Naab spoke, this time vehemently. \"Stop treating God's Word like fast food,\" Dr. Naab challenged, his voice echoing in the quiet room. He said that real growth only happens when the Word moves past the head and into the heart. He told the class that deep roots mean staying planted even when it is uncomfortable, like when they are corrected or when the Holy Spirit begins pruning away their pride.\n\n\"Surface level Christianity is only showing up when it is convenient. It results in shallow roots that cannot hold a person up. True commitment is the only thing that keeps a believer standing when everyone else is being uprooted,\" Dr. Naab explained.\n\nHe went on, and this time Stacey and his friends were much more sober. \"Dare to do big things. Go deeper and bigger. Put yourself in situations that will stretch you. Stretch your faith to the highest point. Do not be comfortable where you are. You are no longer teenagers. Go harder and get your roots into that eternal stream so that no storm can shake you, ensuring you bear fruit in every single season. Come up hither now and always.\".",
