      "Now the serpent was more cunning than any beast of the field which the Lord God had made. And he said to the woman, \"Has God indeed said, 'You shall not eat of every tree of the garden'?\"",
    scriptureReference: "Genesis 3:1 (NKJV)",
    body: "Serpents love the shade. In the natural world, trees provide a cool escape from the scorching sun, and snakes use that cover to hide. Spiritually, the enemy tries to do the same thing by sneaking into the \"shade\" of our church groups and friendships. He waits for the perfect moment to inject his venom, things like doubt, drama, or deep discouragement. If we are not careful, that poison can begin to spread through our lives, affecting how we think and act.\n\nThe good news is that if your roots are deep enough, you are basically \"venom proof.\" A tree whose roots are plunged deep into the river of God, through serious Bible study and prayer, cannot be easily shaken or poisoned. The serpent may try to touch the lower branches, but he cannot reach your hidden life source. When you stay grounded in the eternal waters of God's glory, the enemy's attacks lose their power because you are connected to a source that is far greater than any poison he tries to release. Hallelujah!",
    prayerPoints: [
      "Father, keep my life deeply rooted in You. Protect me from every hidden attack of the enemy and let me remain strong in Your presence.",
    ],
    formattedMessage:
      "*BEWARE OF THE SERPENT II*\n(Stay alert to the cunning ways of the enemy)\n\n\"Now the serpent was more cunning than any beast of the field which the Lord God had made. And he said to the woman, 'Has God indeed said, You shall not eat of every tree of the garden?'\"\n*Genesis 3:1 (NKJV)*\n\n*LEVEL UP*\nSerpents love the shade. In the natural world, trees provide a cool escape from the scorching sun, and snakes use that cover to hide. Spiritually, the enemy tries to do the same thing by sneaking into the \"shade\" of our church groups and friendships. He waits for the perfect moment to inject his venom, things like doubt, drama, or deep discouragement. If we are not careful, that poison can begin to spread through our lives, affecting how we think and act.\n\nThe good news is that if your roots are deep enough, you are basically \"venom proof.\" A tree whose roots are plunged deep into the river of God, through serious Bible study and prayer, cannot be easily shaken or poisoned. The serpent may try to touch the lower branches, but he cannot reach your hidden life source. When you stay grounded in the eternal waters of God's glory, the enemy's attacks lose their power because you are connected to a source that is far greater than any poison he tries to release. Hallelujah!\n\n*PRAYER*\nFather, keep my life deeply rooted in You. Protect me from every hidden attack of the enemy and let me remain strong in Your presence.",
    status: "scheduled",
    monthYear,
