    formattedMessage:
      "*A HEART OF LIFE II*\n(Guard your heart rightly)\n\n\"Stand firm then......with the breastplate of righteousness in place.\"\n*Ephesians 6:14 (NKJV)*\n\n*LEVEL UP*\nDid you know that the armour of God has important elements to guard your heart ? When you got saved, there was a renewal of your mind. Salvation brings a renewal, a restoration, and through the scriptures, we see that working out one's salvation also requires you being transformed by the renewing of your mind. Why? Because the mind creates and influences change, so as the heart.\n\nYoung ancient, when you received salvation, your eyes doesn't change color, neither your skin, but your mind underwent a transformation. Do you see it? Now, in that same reality, righteousness came from believing with the heart. Let's take a quick glance at this verse,\" Romans 10:10. For with the heart one believes unto righteousness, and with the mouth confession is made unto salvation\". So mighty one, if you don't guard your heart right, not only will grief find its way in shaping your life, but your identity as the righteousness of God in Christ can be disrupted and altered. which you may function in accordance to, remember the heart projects who you tend to become. Pay heed!\n\n*PRAYER INSTRUCTIONS*\nDeclare today that your heart is filled with purity and life through the ministry of God's Word, and that God's righteousness resounds in perfect harmony with your heart.",
